#: ../../R/RTFM.rst:5
msgid "RTFM"
msgstr "RTFM"

#: ../../R/RTFM.rst:7
msgid "/R·T·F·M/, imp\\."
msgstr "/R·T·F·M/, 命令法"

#: ../../R/RTFM.rst:9
msgid "[Unix] Abbreviation for ‘Read The Fucking Manual’."
msgstr "[Unix] ‘Read The Fucking Manual’の略。"

#: ../../R/RTFM.rst:12
msgid ""
"Used by :ref:`guru`\\s to brush off questions they consider trivial or "
"annoying. Compare :ref:`Don-t-do-that-then-`\\."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`guru`\\ が、些細あるいは煩わしいと考える質問をはねつけるために使う。\\ :ref:`Don-t-do-that-"
"then-`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../R/RTFM.rst:16
msgid ""
"Used when reporting a problem to indicate that you aren't just asking out of"
" :ref:`randomness`\\. \"No, I can't figure out how to interface Unix to my "
"toaster, and yes, I have RTFM.\" Unlike sense 1, this use is considered "
"polite. See also :ref:`FM`\\, :ref:`RTFAQ`\\, :ref:`RTFB`\\, :ref:`RTFS`\\, "
":ref:`STFW`\\, :ref:`RTM`\\, all of which mutated from RTFM, and compare "
":ref:`UTSL`\\."
msgstr ""
"問題を報告する際に、自分が単に\\ :ref:`randomness`\\ "
"で尋ねているのではないと示すために使う。「いや、Unixをトースターにつなぐ方法がわからないんだ。そうだ、RTFMはした」。語義1とは違い、この用法は丁寧とみなされる。\\"
" :ref:`FM`\\ 、\\ :ref:`RTFAQ`\\ 、\\ :ref:`RTFB`\\ 、\\ :ref:`RTFS`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`STFW`\\ 、\\ :ref:`RTM`\\ も参照。これらはすべてRTFMから変異したものである。\\ :ref:`UTSL`\\ "
"と比較せよ。"
